      "body_md": "## AuditToolkit Windows Security Lite — v0.1.0\n\nAuthenticode-signed MSI installer for Windows host/server security auditing.\n\n### Artifacts\n| File | Notes |\n| --- | --- |\n| `AuditToolkitWinSecLite-0.1.0.msi` | Authenticode-signed (SHA-256, RFC-3161 timestamp) |\n| `audittoolkit-codesign.cer` | Public code-signing certificate (for allow-listing) |\n| `SHA256SUMS` | Integrity checksums |\n\n### Signing & trust\nSigned by **`CN=AuditToolkit Code Signing, O=AuditToolkitLabs`**\n(thumbprint `93708C6494159152678FA51145D15C656F17AD2A`, DigiCert-timestamped).\n\nThis is an AuditToolkit-issued publisher certificate intended for **data-centre /\nserver deployment**. The signature provides tamper-evidence regardless of trust;\nwhere you enforce **WDAC / AppLocker**, allow-list the publisher once using the\nincluded `.cer` (see `docs/WINDOWS-CODE-SIGNING.md`). SmartScreen / S-mode are\nconsumer-desktop features and do not apply to Windows Server / silent installs.\n\n```powershell\nGet-AuthenticodeSignature .\\AuditToolkitWinSecLite-0.1.0.msi | Format-List Status, SignerCertificate\n# Thumbprint must read 93708C6494159152678FA51145D15C656F17AD2A\n```\n\n### Install\n```powershell\nmsiexec /i AuditToolkitWinSecLite-0.1.0.msi /qn /l*v install.log\naudittoolkit-windows-security-lite run\n```\n",
